 <FONT size=4><STRONG> Notes: </FONT></STRONG>
  <HR SIZE=3> <P> <UL>
If DAV ACLs are close to the underlying system model, then they are
</UL><UL>
<LI>  easier to code
</UL><UL>
<LI>  Contain fewer security holes
</UL><UL>
<LI>  More predictable
</UL><UL>
<LI>  Easier to explain, document
</UL><UL>
<LI>
</UL><UL>
There are other  models to emulate, but FSï¿½s are important because there are back doors to accessing data on filesystems.
</UL><UL>
Document repositories are yet other bodies of experience with security; different again from filesystems.
</UL> </P> 

